Usage: check_tracks [-help] [-direction <string>] [-grid <string>]
                    [-layer <string>] [-mask <string>] [-offset <string>]
                    [-origin <string>]

-help                         # Prints out the command usage
-direction <string>           # track direction: horiz | vert | H | V
                              # (string, optional)
-grid <string>                # track spacing (string, optional)
-layer <string>               # track layer (string, optional)
-mask <string>                # mask name (string, optional)
-offset <string>              # track offset from starting point
                              # (string, optional)
-origin <string>              # track starting point: design | core | D | C
                              # (string, optional)